powervigil (1.0.2-1) stable; urgency=critical

  * CRITICAL: Fixed boot failure on UEFI/modern systems
  * Removed acpi=off parameter that breaks hardware detection
  * Removed noapic/nolapic that break USB and storage controllers  
  * Removed other dangerous kernel parameters
  * Systems with v1.0.1 should NOT reboot before applying fix
  * Added emergency-fix-boot.sh for affected systems

 -- Shaun Prince <suparious@solidrust.net>  Wed, 22 Jan 2025 12:00:00 -0700

powervigil (1.0.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Added automatic detection and disabling of conflicting services
  * New powervigil-disable-conflicts utility
  * Fixed debian build process to preserve maintainer scripts
  * Improved verification script conflict detection
  * Added support for disabling power-profiles-daemon and upower

 -- Shaun Prince <suparious@solidrust.net>  Wed, 22 Jan 2025 11:30:00 -0700

